<font color="#FF0000">TO JOHN RATLIFF</font><br>
<tt>Thu Sep  4 23:41:49 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
John,<br><br>
A source I have read, *A Bright Shining Lie*, by Neil Sheehan deals in depth with the overthrow of Diem.<br><br>
The author maintains that Lucien Conein an old hand with the CIA - who had worked with Edward Lansdale in the early days of the Republic of Vietnam - organized the South Vietnamese generals to stage a coup.<br><br>
Henry Cabot Lodge, the US ambassador and President Kennedy knew of the plot also. The US Commanding General Paul Harkins was deliberately kept in the dark because of fears that he would alert Diem.<br><br>
As far as an assassination being ordered by the US, nothing has been proven.<br><br>
Stanley Karnow's book about the history of Vietnam also deals with the coup, but as I recall not in as great of detail as Sheehan's book. At any rate, if my memory serves me correctly, Karnow draws the same conclusion: that there was CIA involvement in the coup. The assassination was not planned.
